# 🚀 Kubernetes (kubectl) Cheat Sheet

## 🔹 1. Cluster & Context

```bash
kubectl cluster-info                # Cluster details
kubectl config view                # View config
kubectl config current-context     # Current context
kubectl config use-context <name>  # Switch context
```

---

## 🔹 2. Nodes

```bash
kubectl get nodes
kubectl describe node <node-name>
kubectl top nodes                  # CPU/memory usage
```

---

## 🔹 3. Pods

```bash
kubectl get pods
kubectl get pods -o wide           # More details
kubectl describe pod <pod-name>
kubectl logs <pod-name>
kubectl logs -f <pod-name>         # Live logs
kubectl exec -it <pod-name> -- bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name>
```

---

## 🔹 4. Namespaces

```bash
kubectl get namespaces
kubectl create namespace <name>
kubectl delete namespace <name>

kubectl get pods -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 5. Deployments

```bash
kubectl get deployments
kubectl create deployment <name> --image=<image>
kubectl describe deployment <name>

kubectl scale deployment <name> --replicas=3
kubectl rollout status deployment <name>
kubectl rollout undo deployment <name>

kubectl delete deployment <name>
```

---

## 🔹 6. Services

```bash
kubectl get svc
kubectl expose deployment <name> --type=NodePort --port=80
kubectl describe svc <service-name>
kubectl delete svc <service-name>
```

---

## 🔹 7. ConfigMaps & Secrets

```bash
kubectl create configmap <name> --from-literal=key=value
kubectl get configmaps

kubectl create secret generic <name> --from-literal=key=value
kubectl get secrets
```

---

## 🔹 8. Files (YAML Apply)

```bash
kubectl apply -f file.yaml
kubectl create -f file.yaml
kubectl delete -f file.yaml
kubectl get all -f file.yaml
```

---

## 🔹 9. Describe & Debug

```bash
kubectl describe <resource> <name>
kubectl get events
kubectl top pods
```

---

## 🔹 10. Port Forwarding

```bash
kubectl port-forward pod/<pod-name> 8080:80
kubectl port-forward svc/<service-name> 8080:80
```

---

## 🔹 11. Labels & Selectors

```bash
kubectl get pods --show-labels
kubectl label pod <pod-name> env=prod
kubectl get pods -l env=prod
```

---

## 🔹 12. Quick Shortcuts (Very Useful 🔥)

```bash
kubectl get po      # pods
kubectl get svc     # services
kubectl get deploy  # deployments
kubectl get ns      # namespaces
kubectl get all
```

---

## 🔹 13. Dry Run & Output

```bash
kubectl run nginx --image=nginx --dry-run=client -o yaml
kubectl get pod <name> -o yaml
kubectl get pod <name> -o json
```

---

## 🔹 14. Delete Everything (Careful ⚠️)

```bash
kubectl delete all --all
```

---

# 💡 Pro Tips (Important for Jobs)

* Always learn **YAML-based deployments** (very important in interviews)
* Use **aliases**:

```bash
alias k=kubectl
```

* Practice on:

  * Minikube
  * Kind (Kubernetes in Docker)

